{
  "text": "In a retrospective analysis of the learning curve (e.g. complications/outcomes) for the first 30 oblique lumbar interbody fusion (OLIF) vs. the first 30 XLIF, [CITATION_1] found there were fewer complications for XLIF (10%) vs. OLIF (33.3%; increased neurovascular trauma). Nevertheless, XLIF still resulted in a 10% significant complication rate [ Table 2 ]. [CITATION_2] Adjacent Table 1 ]. [CITATION_3] On the other hand, Ono et al. (2019) reviewed 21 patients who underwent spinal deformity surgery, and at one postoperative year, XLIF demonstrated a strong ability to reconstruct the deformity [ Table 2 ]. [CITATION_4] ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "104294548",
